    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-03T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-03T10:00:00-05:00" n="325"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d325">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3231/981: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Scotten</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-03T12:00:00-03:00"
                            >August 3, 1935—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received August 3—11:26
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>182. Department’s 126, July 25, 6 p.m.<note n="9" xml:id="d325fn9">Not
                        printed.</note> At the request of the Minister for Foreign Affairs I called
                    upon him this morning. He stated that yesterday afternoon he had had a meeting
                    with the leaders of the majority in the Chamber of Deputies together with the
                    reporter of the Finance Commission which is at present studying the trade
                    agreement. As a result of this meeting he asked me to assure the Department that
                    the trade agreement would be ratified by the end of August.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Scotten</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
